From 8f1d766f22ad3e10b600f1221ca5563a59819269 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: fushi <fushi.peng@nxp.com>
Date: Tue, 16 Sep 2025 14:23:32 +0800
Subject: [PATCH] imx95: Add quad pin nor flash support

As FDRM-MR-iMX95 board use quad pin nor flash W25Q512NWEIQ, so add
one fcb header file iMX95/scripts/fspi_header-W25Q512NWEIQ, current
this fcb header setup flexspi boot with 133M and 1 pad.

The mkimage cmd as below:
make SOC=iMX95 OEI=YES REV=B0 QSPI_HEADER=./scripts/fspi_header-W25Q512NWEIQ flash_lpboot_sm_a55_flexspi

Signed-off-by: fushi <fushi.peng@nxp.com>
Reviewed-by: Ye Li <ye.li@nxp.com>
---
 iMX95/scripts/fspi_header-W25Q512NWEIQ | 128 +++++++++++++++++++++++++
 1 file changed, 128 insertions(+)
 create mode 100644 iMX95/scripts/fspi_header-W25Q512NWEIQ

diff --git a/iMX95/scripts/fspi_header-W25Q512NWEIQ b/iMX95/scripts/fspi_header-W25Q512NWEIQ
new file mode 100644
index 0000000..36cc057
--- /dev/null
+++ b/iMX95/scripts/fspi_header-W25Q512NWEIQ
@@ -0,0 +1,128 @@
